interval-specific cell loss, \verb{L_s(c_j) = R_s(c_\{j-1\}) - R_s(c_j)}. Candidate
intervals are first filtered by absolute cell loss, relative cell loss,
retained cell count, and retained fraction. Retention-loss enrichment is then
evaluated within each sample, p-values are adjusted per sample, and
significant intervals are summarized into sample-level cutoff candidates:
the first significant high-to-low boundary, the largest-drop boundary, and
the selected cutoff under the requested decision mode. When species/tissue or
a user reference is supplied, literature-informed reference cutoffs are added
